00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:08.260
In 1964, a man named Sam
McGee made a new version

00:02:08.260 --> 00:02:13.200
of a tune he'd first recorded
in 1934, Railroad Blues.

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:18.460
And in the way that McGee's
guitar seemed to have 20 strings

00:02:18.460 --> 00:02:23.060
and McGee himself four hands,
he was a whole orchestra.

00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:27.830 position:56%
And the way that he shouted wahoo
as his notes rushed past and the way

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:33.520
that he aimed his voice at the sky
he was standing by himself on top

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:37.650
of a mountain, alone in
the world, not another sign

00:02:37.650 --> 00:02:41.390
of human presence as
far as he could see.

00:02:41.390 --> 00:02:44.120
But whatever image came to mind

00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:48.880
as McGee's Railroad Blues played
you couldn't imagine the man

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:51.150
who was singing standing still.

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:55.900
As the tune played the singer
went from one place to another

00:02:55.900 --> 00:02:58.990
and he was no longer
merely Sam McGee.

00:02:58.990 --> 00:03:01.470
From the first move into the tune

00:03:01.470 --> 00:03:06.480
and almost unbearably
delicious downward swoop

00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:09.350
on a fact-based note making it feel

00:03:09.350 --> 00:03:11.440
as if you were being
lifted off your feet

00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:14.950
from that first gesture
whoever was singing

00:03:14.950 --> 00:03:19.090
and playing the song was somebody
bigger, something more various

00:03:19.090 --> 00:03:22.720
than could ever be
contained in an ordinary name.

00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:25.620
He was Daniel Boone
with faster feet.

00:03:25.620 --> 00:03:29.660
He was Johnny Appleseed
with songs instead of pips.

00:03:29.660 --> 00:03:33.220
He was Cooper's leather
stocking with a sense of humor.

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:39.380
He was Huck Finn as an old man
having long since understood

00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:42.600
as Edmund Wilson wrote in 1922,

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:46.470
