Newport folk festival brought him

01:00:57.010 --> 01:01:00.760
up they made him leave his
electric guitar behind.

01:01:00.760 --> 01:01:04.480
He said they treated him
as if he was the tar baby,

01:01:04.480 --> 01:01:09.420
meaning just a figure from
black folklore not a real person

01:01:09.420 --> 01:01:12.320
who could make his own decisions
about how we wanted to play

01:01:12.320 --> 01:01:14.530
and how he wanted to sound.

01:01:14.530 --> 01:01:19.010
He had to be brought forth as
a representative of the folk

01:01:19.010 --> 01:01:21.950
and the folk didn't
play no electric guitar.

01:01:21.950 --> 01:01:26.440
That's the best way I
can answer it briefly.

01:01:26.440 --> 01:01:32.640
&gt;&gt; So were there any
tensions there [inaudible]?

01:01:32.640 --> 01:01:35.440
&gt;&gt; Greil Marcus: Yeah, I mean
there was tremendous tension.

01:01:35.440 --> 01:01:37.940
I mean you take somebody
like Clarence Ashley,

01:01:37.940 --> 01:01:44.990
somebody like Skip James who were
ordinary disagreeable proud people

01:01:44.990 --> 01:01:51.140
and they were, you know, put in
yo9u know kind of musical forums

01:01:51.140 --> 01:01:55.880
where the whole point would
be to illustrate a genre.

01:01:55.880 --> 01:02:00.440 position:56%
And these people would say I'm not a
genre, you know, this is what I have

01:02:00.440 --> 01:02:03.600 position:56%
